author: sussman
msg: Make the parser's vtable actually build and commit fs transactions.
'svnadmin load' pretty much works now, just a few loose ends to tie up.
* svn_error_codes.h (SVN_ERR_UNRECOGNIZED_STREAM_DATA):  new error code.
* load.c
(parse_content_block): toss the pack_func legacy junk.
(svn_repos_parse_dumpstream): don't pass a pack_func.
(struct parse_baton): add a repos object.
(struct revision_baton): add a txn_root and datestamp.
(make_node_baton): bugfix -- set action field, not kind!
(new_revision_record): start a new txn in the fs.
(new_node_record): parse the node action, do the action.
(set_revision_property, set_node_property):  set the property in the fs.
(close_revision): commit the txn.
